\begin_layout Abstract
From this literature review, we highlight the negligence regarding the treatment given to residential investment. The importance of this component of aggregate demand in determining the economic cycle is highlighted by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "leamer_housing_2007"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and recently taken up by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "fiebiger_semi-autonomous_2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 in which residential investment anticipates the cycle. In this way, we build a Sraffian supermultiplier model (SSM) to emphasize the importance of household investment. However, as 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "brochier_supermultiplier_2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 point out, such model lacks an adequate treatment of financial relations. With this gap in mind, a SSM-Stock-Flow Consistent (thereafter SSM-SFC) is modeled to initiate a research area towards the endogeinization of this autonomous expenditure. The importance of this research is the possibility to analyze the cyclicity of the economy in light of the instability of the aggregate demand as 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
